{"id": "EUVD-2022-55422", "enisaUuid": "df6207e4-54f8-35fe-88ce-a1cab523ed73", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nPCI: microchip: Fix refcount leak in mc_pcie_init_irq_domains()\n\nof_get_next_child() returns a node pointer with refcount incremented, so we\nshould use of_node_put() on it when we don't need it anymore.\n\nmc_pcie_init_irq_domains() only calls of_node_put() in the normal path,\nmissing it in some error paths.  Add missing of_node_put() to avoid\nrefcount leak.", "datePublished": "2025-06-18T12:30:51", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-25T15:31:32", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c0ad5c7e68d10f6f8ffb0f4329e3c19404fbca58", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6cd5f93b5c6a66c68a91dbc604a78207252ecd43", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/880ece912b958a0c92cc0baa8e906fb9b49a4b53", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f030304fdeb87ec8f1b518c73703214aec6cc24a", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50157"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50157"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "053b3c3d-859f-3e14-b255-ffa6976dfe40", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6f15a9c9f94133bee0d861a4bf25e10aaa95219d <c0ad5c7e68d10f6f8ffb0f4329e3c19404fbca58"}, {"id": "1d9e6232-3769-32eb-8b40-bd4755aff4f0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6f15a9c9f94133bee0d861a4bf25e10aaa95219d <6cd5f93b5c6a66c68a91dbc604a78207252ecd43"}, {"id": "2ccf6e1c-4463-386d-a0db-e0039b148ddb", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "62791ecb-f9df-3ba9-8810-0973d3a384f9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6f15a9c9f94133bee0d861a4bf25e10aaa95219d <880ece912b958a0c92cc0baa8e906fb9b49a4b53"}, {"id": "69ac8520-b960-30c9-b86d-7c1342aadbe3", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0"}, {"id": "7a613e37-2a08-33c2-b9b8-7b4b0e221e18", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19.2"}, {"id": "ae69f750-8fbf-375c-a8af